<div class=3D"section" id=3D"restricted-data-your-telemetry-setting">
<h4>Restricted data (Your Telemetry setting)<a class=3D"headerlink" href=3D=
"https://f1-2020-telemetry.readthedocs.io/en/stable/telemetry-specification=
.html#restricted-data-your-telemetry-setting" title=3D"Permalink to this he=
adline">=C2=B6</a></h4>
<p>There is some data in the UDP that you may not want other players seeing=
 if you are in a multiplayer game.
This is controlled by the =E2=80=9CYour Telemetry=E2=80=9D setting in the T=
elemetry options.
The options are:</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>Restricted (Default) =E2=80=93 other players viewing the UDP data wi=
ll not see values for your car</p></li>
<li><p>Public =E2=80=93 all other players can see all the data for your car=
</p></li>
</ul>
<p>Note: You can always see the data for the car you are driving regardless=
 of the setting.</p>
<p>The following data items are set to zero if the player driving the car i=
n question has their =E2=80=9CYour Telemetry=E2=80=9D set to =E2=80=9CRestr=
icted=E2=80=9D:</p>
<p class=3D"rubric">Car status packet</p>
<ul class=3D"simple">
<li><p>m_fuelInTank</p></li>
<li><p>m_fuelCapacity</p></li>
<li><p>m_fuelMix</p></li>
<li><p>m_fuelRemainingLaps</p></li>
<li><p>m_frontBrakeBias</p></li>
<li><p>m_frontLeftWingDamage</p></li>
<li><p>m_frontRightWingDamage</p></li>
<li><p>m_rearWingDamage</p></li>
<li><p>m_engineDamage</p></li>
<li><p>m_gearBoxDamage</p></li>
<li><p>m_tyresWear (All four wheels)</p></li>
<li><p>m_tyresDamage (All four wheels)</p></li>
<li><p>m_ersDeployMode</p></li>
<li><p>m_ersStoreEnergy</p></li>
<li><p>m_ersDeployedThisLap</p></li>
<li><p>m_ersHarvestedThisLapMGUK</p></li>
<li><p>m_ersHarvestedThisLapMGUH</p></li>
<li><p>m_tyresAgeLaps</p></li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
